narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: THIS IS THE BEST CLASS EVER. take it take it. hard language very easy class. the pace is very slow and the work is very very manageable (30 min/night if even). if you like languages, she will give you bonus material on the side if you want to go faster. KvK is the best!!

I think Czech 110 is a great class that I would recommended to anyone at Yale. However it is important to know that although it is a level one language class a lot of linguists were in my class making the learning speed a little quicker.

If you're serious about learning Czech, be warned that a lot of people who take this class are not. You will certainly learn the language, but you have to put a lot in to get a lot out. I love the Czech language, so if you think you can put up with a distractions, definitely take this class.
